133
00:09:08.551 --> 00:09:10.951
I opened everything and now I have to put everything back again.

134
00:09:10.951 --> 00:09:14.351
You checked that folding pipe chair too, didn't you?

135
00:09:14.351 --> 00:09:16.351
No, not yet for fingerprints.

136
00:09:16.351 --> 00:09:18.351
We were going to take it back with us and check it.

137
00:09:18.351 --> 00:09:21.251
The other forensic officer is taking it along together with the mic stand.

138
00:09:21.251 --> 00:09:22.351
Excuse me,

139
00:09:22.351 --> 00:09:24.951
but could I have a look at the underside of the seat?

140
00:09:24.951 --> 00:09:27.151
What? Okay, please be quick about it.

141
00:09:27.151 --> 00:09:29.051
Thank you.

142
00:09:32.451 --> 00:09:33.651
Just as I thought.

143
00:09:33.651 --> 00:09:35.951
So, that's the story.

144
00:09:38.151 --> 00:09:40.851
Things look pretty bad.

145
00:09:40.851 --> 00:09:42.251
Yes.

146
00:09:42.251 --> 00:09:43.951
Excuse me, I'm coming through.

147
00:09:44.751 --> 00:09:46.451
Excuse me. Please let me through.

148
00:09:47.351 --> 00:09:49.551
Excuse me. Please let me through.

149
00:09:50.151 --> 00:09:52.651
Excuse me. Please let me through.

150
00:09:54.051 --> 00:09:56.551
That's right. I remember back then,

151
00:09:56.551 --> 00:09:59.951
a mysterious lady tried to kidnap Conan and Ai...

152
00:10:00.951 --> 00:10:04.351
Come on and move away from that brunette.

153
00:10:04.351 --> 00:10:06.451
If you don't want to die, quickly!

154
00:10:06.451 --> 00:10:08.351
Come on, quickly!

155
00:10:08.351 --> 00:10:10.351
Move it, Angel!

156
00:10:11.451 --> 00:10:14.351
She called me that.

157
00:10:14.351 --> 00:10:19.951
But why did Azusa call me the same way that lady did?

158
00:10:29.417 --> 00:10:31.017
You figured it out?

159
00:10:31.017 --> 00:10:34.117
The trick that the perp used to hang Mr. Hado up?

160
00:10:34.117 --> 00:10:35.417
Are you serious?

161
00:10:35.417 --> 00:10:37.217
Yes, I think so.

162
00:10:37.217 --> 00:10:41.317
So, we passed the rope through the spotlight bar,

163
00:10:41.317 --> 00:10:43.317
then tied one side of the rope

164
00:10:43.317 --> 00:10:47.017
onto Officer Takagi who is sitting in the chair.

165
00:10:47.017 --> 00:10:48.517
But, are you sure that it will take just one person

166
00:10:48.517 --> 00:10:50.217
to suspend him in mid air?

167
00:10:50.217 --> 00:10:51.817
Of course.

168
00:10:51.817 --> 00:10:53.717
First, you create a loop with the rope

169
00:10:53.717 --> 00:10:55.617
hanging from the bar on the stage

170
00:10:55.617 --> 00:10:58.217
and make a knot like this.

171
00:10:58.217 --> 00:10:59.717
Then pass the rope below from the foreground under the rope at the top

172
00:10:59.717 --> 00:11:02.917
and wrap the bottom loop around the top loop two times.

173
00:11:02.917 --> 00:11:06.217
Twist the loop on the bottom as you pull it through the loop.

174
00:11:06.217 --> 00:11:10.917
Pass the section hanging down through the loop.

175
00:11:10.917 --> 00:11:12.717
Hook the resulting large loop

176
00:11:12.717 --> 00:11:16.617
onto the armrest of the seat about two meter below.

177
00:11:16.617 --> 00:11:18.417
Like this.

178
00:11:18.417 --> 00:11:21.017
Next, pass the end of the rope

179
00:11:21.017 --> 00:11:23.717
without the loops under the armrest.

180
00:11:23.717 --> 00:11:26.017
Create the same loops as before and pass the rope through.

181
00:11:26.017 --> 00:11:28.617
Now, hook the large loop and rope

182
00:11:28.617 --> 00:11:31.917
on the armrest of a chair about four meters away.

183
00:11:31.917 --> 00:11:35.717
Create the third look and pass the rope through,

184
00:11:35.717 --> 00:11:40.817
and this time, hook the large loop onto a chair

185
00:11:40.817 --> 00:11:42.817
about eight meters away.

186
00:11:42.817 --> 00:11:44.217
Now, all you have to do is

187
00:11:44.217 --> 00:11:49.717
return to the third set of small loops you created

188
00:11:49.717 --> 00:11:52.117
and pull on the leftover rope.

189
00:11:52.117 --> 00:11:54.217
Sonoko, since you look to be the weakest,

190
00:11:54.217 --> 00:11:55.717
will you pull the rope, please?

191
00:11:55.717 --> 00:11:59.217
Who, me?

192
00:11:59.217 --> 00:12:01.017
Okay.

193
00:12:02.417 --> 00:12:05.317
I don't think I'll be able to lift him up, though.

194
00:12:10.317 --> 00:12:11.717
What the?

195
00:12:11.717 --> 00:12:13.617
What's going on?

196
00:12:13.617 --> 00:12:16.617
Principle of the pulley. Correct?

197
00:12:16.617 --> 00:12:18.017
Yes.

198
00:12:18.017 --> 00:12:19.117
The small loop that was made partway

199
00:12:19.117 --> 00:12:22.317
through the rope functioned as a pulley.

200
00:12:22.317 --> 00:12:23.817
Each loop makes it possible for the rope

201
00:12:23.817 --> 00:12:28.417
to be pulled at two times, four times, or eight times the power.

202
00:12:28.417 --> 00:12:31.417
It's actually not a pulley but the loop of a rope,

203
00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:34.117
so due to friction 8 times is not possible,

204
00:12:34.117 --> 00:12:36.317
but if a light and slippery rope is used,

205
00:12:36.317 --> 00:12:39.717
even Sonoko can lift Officer Takagi up.

206
00:12:39.717 --> 00:12:43.017
This means that not many,

207
00:12:43.017 --> 00:12:46.517
but just one person lifted Mr. Hado up.

208
00:12:46.517 --> 00:12:51.417
This is the way that couriers tie their rope

209
00:12:51.417 --> 00:12:53.917
and fix their loads on securely.

210
00:12:53.917 --> 00:12:56.817
In other words, the one most suspicious of being the perp

211
00:12:56.817 --> 00:12:59.317
that lifted Mr. Hado up is

212
00:12:59.317 --> 00:13:02.717
the one who used to work at a courier company in her younger days...

213
00:13:02.717 --> 00:13:04.917
Mr. Hado's manager.

214
00:13:06.017 --> 00:13:10.517
You, Ms. Kanae Enjo.

215
00:13:10.517 --> 00:13:12.317
Okay, maybe she lifted him up,

216
00:13:12.317 --> 00:13:15.117
but how did she tie the rope onto the seats?

217
00:13:15.117 --> 00:13:17.917
That's easy.

218
00:13:17.917 --> 00:13:20.317
After lifting him up,

219
00:13:20.317 --> 00:13:22.017
she ties the tip of the rope to a seat nearby temporarily

220
00:13:22.017 --> 00:13:24.017
and sets it in place.

221
00:13:24.017 --> 00:13:26.417
She twists a wire into this part of the rope

222
00:13:26.417 --> 00:13:29.417
that's hanging from above.

223
00:13:29.417 --> 00:13:30.517
If she fixes the rope

224
00:13:30.517 --> 00:13:33.117
that is hanging from the ceiling in place with the wire,

225
00:13:33.117 --> 00:13:35.117
next all she has to do is untie the extra rope

226
00:13:35.117 --> 00:13:38.617
and tie it on again to the seat, then remove the wire.

227
00:13:38.617 --> 00:13:40.817
The good thing about this courier tying method is

228
00:13:40.817 --> 00:13:44.517
no knot is tied anywhere so it's easy to untie.

229
00:13:44.517 --> 00:13:46.117
But if a new rope were used,

230
00:13:46.117 --> 00:13:49.017
marks would be left behind on the rope.

231
00:13:49.017 --> 00:13:52.517
That's why after she retied the rope to the seat,

232
00:13:52.517 --> 00:13:54.517
she cut off the extra rope with a cutter

233
00:13:54.517 --> 00:13:55.917
that was in the tool box and coiled the rope.

234
00:13:55.917 --> 00:13:57.817
She then put it next to the tool box

235
00:13:57.817 --> 00:14:01.817
that was at the sleeve of the stage, correct?

236
00:14:01.817 --> 00:14:03.817
Ms. Enjo?

237
00:14:03.817 --> 00:14:07.817
Hey, hey. Just because she part-timed at a courier before,

238
00:14:07.817 --> 00:14:11.317
to accuse her of being the perp just because of that is...

239
00:14:11.317 --> 00:14:13.817
It's the size of her feet.

240
00:14:13.817 --> 00:14:18.217
-Feet? -Couriers coil the rope around like this

241
00:14:18.217 --> 00:14:21.817
and bundle the rope.

242
00:14:21.817 --> 00:14:24.017
The inside loop of the rope that is coiled

243
00:14:24.017 --> 00:14:25.417
is approximately the same size

244
00:14:25.417 --> 00:14:27.317
as the feet of the person who coiled the rope!

245
00:14:27.317 --> 00:14:29.317
The length from the elbow to the wrist

246
00:14:29.317 --> 00:14:31.817
is the size of that person's feet.

247
00:14:31.817 --> 00:14:33.317
The loop of the rope at the scene

248
00:14:33.317 --> 00:14:37.217
was coiled in just about the size of Ran's feet

249
00:14:37.217 --> 00:14:39.317
so I just thought that the rope might have been

250
00:14:39.317 --> 00:14:42.617
tied by the manager who is of small built.

251
00:14:42.617 --> 00:14:44.317
I see.

252
00:14:44.317 --> 00:14:47.317
The feelings that the Ms. Beauty felt for Hado

253
00:14:47.317 --> 00:14:51.017
turned into a grudge over a span of 17 years.

254
00:14:51.017 --> 00:14:53.517
Hey! Stop making rude remarks!

255
00:14:53.517 --> 00:14:56.017
We don't know if she's the one who did it.

256
00:14:56.017 --> 00:14:58.817
Contact lenses.

257
00:14:58.817 --> 00:15:01.417
I'm sure you must've noticed because you're his manager,

258
00:15:01.417 --> 00:15:03.517
that Mr. Hado was wearing circle contact lens

259
00:15:03.517 --> 00:15:05.417
to make his iris look bigger.

260
00:15:05.417 --> 00:15:06.717
Yes.

261
00:15:06.717 --> 00:15:08.917
When I compared Mr. Hado's driver's license picture

262
00:15:08.917 --> 00:15:12.117
to the picture that the magazine reporter took of Mr. Hado today,

263
00:15:12.117 --> 00:15:14.217
even I could tell.

