00:15:15.317 --> 00:15:17.717
One of the lens

265
00:15:17.717 --> 00:15:20.217
is stuck to your back, Manager.

266
00:15:20.217 --> 00:15:21.617
What?

267
00:15:25.317 --> 00:15:27.117
This is...

268
00:15:27.117 --> 00:15:28.817
May I?

269
00:15:28.817 --> 00:15:30.617
Yes.

270
00:15:30.617 --> 00:15:32.217
I see.

271
00:15:32.217 --> 00:15:34.917
When you lifted him up,

272
00:15:34.917 --> 00:15:37.717
it unfortunately probably dropped onto your clothes.

273
00:15:37.717 --> 00:15:39.717
We've got enough evidence.

274
00:15:39.717 --> 00:15:41.317
We'll hear the rest out at the station.

275
00:15:41.317 --> 00:15:43.817
Wait. Did you really do it?

276
00:15:43.817 --> 00:15:48.217
Why did you have to kill the man that you supported for 17 years?

277
00:15:48.217 --> 00:15:50.517
Please answer me.

278
00:15:50.517 --> 00:15:51.917
She wouldn't be able to answer that question

279
00:15:51.917 --> 00:15:53.817
no matter how much you ask.

280
00:15:53.817 --> 00:15:57.617
Because she didn't kill him.

281
00:15:58.517 --> 00:15:59.617
What?

282
00:15:59.617 --> 00:16:01.517
Just what are you talking about?

283
00:16:01.517 --> 00:16:06.117
Where do you think the other circle lens was?

284
00:16:06.117 --> 00:16:08.517
It was stuck on the back of the seat of the folding pipe chair

285
00:16:08.517 --> 00:16:10.917
that was left at the sleeve of the stage.

286
00:16:10.917 --> 00:16:13.117
In other words, the chair was on the floor

287
00:16:13.117 --> 00:16:16.117
right below where he was hung at his feet.

288
00:16:16.117 --> 00:16:20.817
Furthermore, the baseball with the kite string tied onto it.

289
00:16:20.817 --> 00:16:25.317
The other tip of the kite string was tied onto the tip of the rope.

290
00:16:25.317 --> 00:16:27.217
Then the ball was thrown to pass the kite string

291
00:16:27.217 --> 00:16:28.517
through the bar on the ceiling,

292
00:16:28.517 --> 00:16:30.217
so that by pulling the kite string,

293
00:16:30.217 --> 00:16:33.517
the rope would be passed over the bar.

294
00:16:33.517 --> 00:16:34.617
No offense,

295
00:16:34.617 --> 00:16:39.517
but I don't think Ms. Enjo can throw the ball high enough over the bar.

296
00:16:39.517 --> 00:16:41.517
If it were Mr. Hado, who played baseball during his high school days

297
00:16:41.517 --> 00:16:43.717
and had a powerful shoulder, it's a different story, though.

298
00:16:43.717 --> 00:16:46.317
"I'm sorry" -And the memo that was found

299
00:16:46.317 --> 00:16:49.117
in Mr. Hado's chest pocket written in his own handwriting.

300
00:16:49.117 --> 00:16:51.117
You know what I'm getting at, don't you?

301
00:16:51.117 --> 00:16:53.417
Don't tell me that he took...

302
00:16:53.417 --> 00:16:56.617
Right. He hung himself.

303
00:16:56.617 --> 00:16:58.217
She found him

304
00:16:58.217 --> 00:17:00.917
and tried to make it look as if he was murdered.

305
00:17:00.917 --> 00:17:03.317
Hey, why did you hide the suicide?

306
00:17:03.317 --> 00:17:06.617
So, something did happen 17 years ago, right?

307
00:17:06.617 --> 00:17:09.117
Don't tell me that he got all chewed up

308
00:17:09.117 --> 00:17:10.917
about what I told him the other day?

309
00:17:10.917 --> 00:17:12.417
What did you tell him?

310
00:17:12.417 --> 00:17:14.917
Actually, 17 years ago,

311
00:17:14.917 --> 00:17:17.217
she was pregnant with Hado's child.

312
00:17:17.217 --> 00:17:18.917
Mr. Fuse!

313
00:17:18.917 --> 00:17:21.517
Saying that it was for the sake of his child who was going to be born,

314
00:17:21.517 --> 00:17:23.717
Hado, who just debuted confined himself in the studio

315
00:17:23.717 --> 00:17:26.217
and continued composing songs,

316
00:17:26.217 --> 00:17:27.417
to the point where it looked as if he would die

317
00:17:27.417 --> 00:17:29.817
from consecutively staying up all night.

318
00:17:29.817 --> 00:17:31.317
So, she went to ask him to stop,

319
00:17:31.317 --> 00:17:35.417
but collapsed on the floor in front of the studio and miscarried.

320
00:17:35.417 --> 00:17:38.517
Then, at the hospital,

321
00:17:38.517 --> 00:17:41.817
she told me not to tell Hado what happened.

322
00:17:41.817 --> 00:17:44.717
I see. The title of the song back then

323
00:17:44.717 --> 00:17:47.517
that he made for the unborn child was "ASACA",

324
00:17:47.517 --> 00:17:48.817
but no lyrics were made for that song

325
00:17:48.817 --> 00:17:51.617
and it was shelved for 17 years.

326
00:17:51.617 --> 00:17:54.317
After finding out what happened, he felt responsible for what happened,

327
00:17:54.317 --> 00:17:57.717
decides to write lyrics for it and release the song.

328
00:17:57.717 --> 00:18:00.117
However, no matter how hard he tried, he couldn't write,

329
00:18:00.117 --> 00:18:04.717
so he wrote a message "I'm sorry" and chose to die.

330
00:18:04.717 --> 00:18:09.117
But, why did you need to make it look like a murder?

331
00:18:09.117 --> 00:18:13.017
I didn't want his family to find out that he committed suicide

332
00:18:13.017 --> 00:18:16.517
because of his ex-girl's unborn child.

333
00:18:16.517 --> 00:18:21.017
That's why I took his cell phone that was in his pocket

334
00:18:21.017 --> 00:18:24.617
that had the call history of his mail that said, "Bye".

335
00:18:24.617 --> 00:18:28.417
I wanted him to soar high to the heavens.

336
00:18:32.917 --> 00:18:36.417
He's dead and yet he makes women cry. What an idiot.

337
00:18:37.417 --> 00:18:41.317
Please don't write an article on this!

338
00:18:41.317 --> 00:18:44.417
I pursued Hado for so many years, you know.

339
00:18:44.417 --> 00:18:48.217
Day after day, I crawled over the ground looking for an article.

340
00:18:48.217 --> 00:18:50.417
And the great scoop that I finally get hold of

341
00:18:50.417 --> 00:18:52.517
turns out to be Hado's greatest scandal of his life.

342
00:18:52.517 --> 00:18:55.417
Please don't! Please!

343
00:18:55.417 --> 00:18:59.217
I think I know Hado better than anyone else.

344
00:18:59.217 --> 00:19:01.417
I wouldn't write about him even if you asked me to.

345
00:19:02.417 --> 00:19:06.917
Sentimental stories don't jive with rock and rollers.

346
00:19:09.517 --> 00:19:12.417
But everything's still a mystery.

347
00:19:12.417 --> 00:19:15.817
I wonder why the "CA" of "ASACA" was written with "C" instead of a "K"?

348
00:19:15.817 --> 00:19:18.817
I've asked Hado about it before.

349
00:19:18.817 --> 00:19:20.417
He heard about the pregnancy

350
00:19:20.417 --> 00:19:22.017
at a morning cafe after he stayed up all night,

351
00:19:22.017 --> 00:19:24.017
so he said if it's a girl, it'd be written "Asaca" in Chinese characters

352
00:19:24.017 --> 00:19:26.917
or if in alphabet, it would be spelled "ASACA"

353
00:19:26.917 --> 00:19:28.717
after the word morning cafe.

354
00:19:28.717 --> 00:19:30.917
I see! I'm convinced!

355
00:19:30.917 --> 00:19:33.217
But despite you being a super close friend to him,

356
00:19:33.217 --> 00:19:34.917
so close that he would tell you all this,

357
00:19:34.917 --> 00:19:38.617
how is it that you turn your back on him and push him into resigning?

358
00:19:38.617 --> 00:19:41.317
Maybe you knew about the guy in his back band

359
00:19:41.317 --> 00:19:44.317
that was nabbed by the narcs a while ago?

360
00:19:44.317 --> 00:19:48.317
I... I don't know anything about that.

361
00:19:48.317 --> 00:19:51.217
My, you sure have quick ears.

362
00:19:51.217 --> 00:19:55.217
No, no. The news is already on the internet.

363
00:19:55.217 --> 00:19:58.217
He's really something.

364
00:19:58.217 --> 00:20:00.617
You're really something, Scotch.

365
00:20:00.617 --> 00:20:02.717
To pretend that you were knocked down by me

366
00:20:02.717 --> 00:20:05.017
and during that time you pulled my gun out.

367
00:20:05.017 --> 00:20:07.617
I don't mean to ask you to spare me,

368
00:20:07.617 --> 00:20:11.117
but won't you hear me out before you shoot me?

369
00:20:11.117 --> 00:20:15.117
I didn't take your gun to shoot you.

370
00:20:15.117 --> 00:20:16.517
I see.

371
00:20:22.417 --> 00:20:24.917
But to do this!

372
00:20:24.917 --> 00:20:26.117
Impossible.

373
00:20:28.717 --> 00:20:33.017
It's humanly impossible to pull the trigger

374
00:20:33.017 --> 00:20:37.017
when you're holding the cylinder of the revolver.

375
00:20:37.017 --> 00:20:39.717
Forget about killing yourself.

376
00:20:39.717 --> 00:20:42.217
You're not meant to die here.

377
00:20:42.217 --> 00:20:43.517
What?

378
00:20:43.517 --> 00:20:47.317
I'm Shuichi Akai who have infiltrated here from the FBI.

379
00:20:47.317 --> 00:20:51.517
I'm a dog just like you who wants to sink my teeth into them.

380
00:20:51.517 --> 00:20:56.317
So now that you know, let go of the gun and hear me out.

381
00:20:56.317 --> 00:21:00.717
It's no problem letting you get away.

382
00:21:00.717 --> 00:21:02.217
Okay.

383
00:21:15.117 --> 00:21:16.717
I see.

384
00:21:16.717 --> 00:21:20.817
He fired the gun to break this.

385
00:21:20.817 --> 00:21:25.817
This cell phone that would have had the data of his family and friends.

386
00:21:31.317 --> 00:21:36.217
Traitor's shall be punished.

387
00:21:36.217 --> 00:21:37.917
Right?

388
00:21:40.617 --> 00:21:42.417
That high neck of yours.

389
00:21:42.417 --> 00:21:46.517
I'm overtaken by the impulse of wanting to pull it down right here.

390
00:21:46.517 --> 00:21:49.817
But I guess I won't do it now.

391
00:21:49.817 --> 00:21:51.417
One day...

392
00:21:53.517 --> 00:21:55.217
I will.

393
00:23:21.017 --> 00:23:23.517
Azusa!

394
00:23:23.517 --> 00:23:25.117
What?

395
00:23:25.117 --> 00:23:29.817
Rather, you aren't Azusa, are you?

396
00:23:29.817 --> 00:23:31.817
Most probably I'm sure...

397
00:23:31.817 --> 00:23:35.017
you're the one who called me angel.

398
00:23:35.017 --> 00:23:37.017
I've told you before, Ran.

399
00:23:37.017 --> 00:23:40.117
Don't get any closer than you are now.

400
00:23:41.317 --> 00:23:45.317
Because you are my treasure.

401
00:23:46.717 --> 00:23:48.317
Right,

402
00:23:48.317 --> 00:23:53.917
the only two treasures I have in this world.

403
00:23:54.417 --> 00:23:55.617
"Next Episode"

404
00:23:55.617 --> 00:23:59.017
-Awesome! -It's really spectacular!

405
00:23:59.017 --> 00:24:01.417
Where are you going to put all these books?

406
00:24:01.417 --> 00:24:05.417
This shop is bursting with books that won't sell!

407
00:24:05.417 --> 00:24:08.417
Meeting an antique book is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity, you know.

408
00:24:08.417 --> 00:24:09.717
I'm sure that they will someday

409
00:24:09.717 --> 00:24:13.617
